 {"id":"coding_agent_usage_tracker-4n4","title":"Prediction: Add time-to-limit display in usage output","description":"## Task Overview

Integrate time-to-limit predictions into the standard `caut usage` output, showing users when they'll hit their limit at current pace.

## Parent EPIC
[EPIC] Time-to-Limit Prediction (coding_agent_usage_tracker-swp)

## Display Design

### Human Output
```
Claude: 65% used
        ├─ Resets in: 2h 30m
        ├─ At current pace: ~1h 45m until limit ⚠️
        └─ Recommendation: Slow down to avoid hitting limit

Codex: 45% used
       ├─ Resets in: 2h 30m
       └─ At current pace: Sustainable ✓
```

### Warning Levels

```rust
enum PredictionStatus {
    /// Will hit limit before reset - urgent
    WillHitLimit { minutes: i32 },
    /// Close to hitting limit (within 20% of reset time)
    MayHitLimit { minutes: i32 },
    /// Sustainable - won't hit limit before reset
    Sustainable,
    /// Usage decreasing
    Decreasing,
    /// Insufficient data to predict
    Unknown,
}
```

### Visual Indicators

- 🔴 `⚠️ ~45m until limit` - Will definitely hit
- 🟡 `~2h until limit` - May hit, close call
- 🟢 `Sustainable ✓` - Safe
- ⬇️ `↘ Decreasing` - Usage going down
- ❓ `Unknown` - Insufficient data

## Implementation

```rust
// src/render/prediction.rs

pub fn render_prediction(
    usage: &UsageSnapshot,
    velocity: Option<f64>,
) -> Vec<String> {
    let mut lines = vec![];

    // Get reset time
    let reset_minutes = usage.primary
        .as_ref()
        .and_then(|p| p.resets_at)
        .map(|t| (t - Utc::now()).num_minutes() as i32)
        .unwrap_or(0);

    let current_pct = usage.primary
        .as_ref()
        .map(|p| p.used_percent)
        .unwrap_or(0.0);

    // Calculate prediction
    let prediction = match velocity {
        Some(v) if v <= 0.0 => PredictionStatus::Decreasing,
        Some(v) => {
            let remaining = 100.0 - current_pct;
            let minutes_to_limit = (remaining / v * 60.0) as i32;

            if minutes_to_limit < reset_minutes {
                if minutes_to_limit < reset_minutes / 5 {
                    PredictionStatus::WillHitLimit { minutes: minutes_to_limit }
                } else {
                    PredictionStatus::MayHitLimit { minutes: minutes_to_limit }
                }
            } else {
                PredictionStatus::Sustainable
            }
        }
        None => PredictionStatus::Unknown,
    };

    // Format output
    lines.push(format!("├─ Resets in: {}", format_duration(reset_minutes)));

    match prediction {
        PredictionStatus::WillHitLimit { minutes } => {
            lines.push(format!(
                "├─ At current pace: ~{} until limit ⚠️",
                format_duration(minutes)
            ));
            lines.push("└─ Recommendation: Slow down to avoid hitting limit".into());
        }
        PredictionStatus::MayHitLimit { minutes } => {
            lines.push(format!(
                "└─ At current pace: ~{} until limit",
                format_duration(minutes)
            ));
        }
        PredictionStatus::Sustainable => {
            lines.push("└─ At current pace: Sustainable ✓".into());
        }
        PredictionStatus::Decreasing => {
            lines.push("└─ Trend: ↘ Usage decreasing".into());
        }
        PredictionStatus::Unknown => {
            lines.push("└─ Prediction: Insufficient data".into());
        }
    }

    lines
}

fn format_duration(minutes: i32) -> String {
    if minutes < 60 {
        format!("{}m", minutes)
    } else if minutes < 1440 {
        format!("{}h {}m", minutes / 60, minutes % 60)
    } else {
        format!("{}d {}h", minutes / 1440, (minutes % 1440) / 60)
    }
}
```

